Sixteen people were seriously injured when a taxi rear-ended a bus on the R36 in Tzaneen, Limpopo on Tuesday.ER24 paramedics responded to the accident where they found a taxi partially wedged beneath the rear of the bus. The entire front of the taxi was completely smashed.&#8220;On assessment, paramedics found that 16 people had been injured in the collision, one critically lay trapped inside the taxi.&#8221; ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring.The bus was empty at the time of the collision except for the bus driver who was not injured, one patient was trapped in the taxi, but paramedics provided the critically injured man with advanced life support interventions.Meiring said rescue services had to separate the taxi from the bus before they could use the jaws-of-life to free the trapped passenger.The injured were taken to different hospitals in Tzaneen for treatment. Investigations are still underway.-TNA Reporter